📌 Project Overview
A complete, production-grade data analytics project analysing 55,500 patient records across 6 medical conditions, 5 insurance providers, and 6 years (2019–2024).
This project covers the full analytics pipeline:
```
Raw Data Ingestion  →  Python EDA  →  SQL Analytics Layer  →  Power BI Dashboard  →  Executive PDF Report
```
Built to demonstrate industry-level skills in data cleaning, exploratory data analysis, SQL querying, business intelligence, and data storytelling.
---
📊 Dataset at a Glance
<div align="center">
Metric	Value
🧑‍⚕️ Total Patients	`55,500`
💰 Total Revenue	`$1.42 Billion`
🧾 Average Billing	`$25,590 per patient`
🛏️ Avg Length of Stay	`15.5 days`
🔬 Abnormal Test Rate	`33.6%`
📅 Date Range	`2019 – 2024`
🦠 Medical Conditions	`6` (Cancer, Diabetes, Obesity, Asthma, Hypertension, Arthritis)
🏦 Insurance Providers	`5` (Cigna, Medicare, Blue Cross, UnitedHealthcare, Aetna)
</div>
---
💡 Key Findings
<details open>
<summary><b>🔍 Click to expand findings</b></summary>
<br/>
> ### 🔴 Finding 1 — Obesity Is the Most Expensive Condition
> Average billing of **$25,860** — highest across all 6 conditions. Cost-per-day of **$3,456** also leads the dataset.
> ### 📉 Finding 2 — Billing & Length of Stay Are Uncorrelated
> Pearson correlation of **-0.006** — effectively zero. Cost is driven by **condition severity and treatment type**, not duration.
> ### ⚖️ Finding 3 — All Five Insurers Carry Equal Financial Load
> Revenue ranges from **$278.9M (Aetna)** to **$287.2M (Cigna)** — a spread of under 3%. Volume is equally balanced.
> ### 🧪 Finding 4 — One-Third of Patients Have Abnormal Test Results
> **33.6%** overall abnormal rate. Arthritis **(34.3%)** and Diabetes **(34.0%)** lead — a critical clinical quality signal.
> ### 🚨 Finding 5 — Emergency Admissions Are High at 32.9%
> Near-equal split across Emergency **(32.9%)**, Urgent **(33.4%)**, and Elective **(33.5%)** — indicating high acute care burden.
> ### ⚠️ Finding 6 — 108 Negative Billing Records Flagged
> Total value: **-$130,472**. Likely insurance credits or refunds. Retained for audit, excluded from financial aggregations.
</details>
