---
📓 Notebooks
`01_data_cleaning.ipynb`
> Input: `healthcare_dataset.csv` (15 cols) → Output: `healthcare_cleaned.csv` (26 cols)
🐛 Issue Found	✅ Fix Applied
Inconsistent name casing (`Bobby JacksOn`)	`.str.title()` on Name, Doctor
Dates stored as strings	Converted to `datetime64`
108 negative billing records	Flagged as `refund_or_credit`, retained
No length of stay column	Engineered `length_of_stay` in days
No age segmentation	`age_group` with 4 bins
No time components	Year, month, quarter, day of week
No cost efficiency metric	`cost_per_day = billing ÷ LOS`
No outcome encoding	`test_result_score`: 0 / 1 / 2
No high-cost identifier	`high_billing_flag` at 90th percentile
`02_eda_demographics.ipynb`
> 6 visualisations — age distribution, gender by condition, blood type heatmap, admission type breakdown, day-of-week patterns, age group × condition matrix.
`03_eda_diagnosis.ipynb`
> 5 visualisations — condition frequency, YoY trends (2019–2024), monthly seasonality heatmap, test result outcomes, medication usage, length of stay boxplots.
`04_eda_financial.ipynb`
> 6 visualisations — billing by condition, insurance revenue, billing vs LOS scatter, admission type financial impact, high-cost patient segment, cost-per-day analysis.
---
🗄️ SQL Layer
Schema — 8 Normalised Tables
```
patients · admissions · billing · hospitals
doctors · medical_conditions · insurance_providers · medications
```
Sample — Diagnosis Query
```sql
-- Top diagnoses by frequency with ranking
SELECT
    medical_condition,
    COUNT(*) AS patient_count,
    ROUND(COUNT(*) * 100.0 / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER(), 2) AS pct_of_total,
    RANK() OVER (ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rank
FROM healthcare
GROUP BY medical_condition
ORDER BY patient_count DESC;
```
Sample — Financial Query
```sql
-- Insurance provider revenue and avg claim
SELECT
    insurance_provider,
    COUNT(*) AS patient_count,
    ROUND(SUM(billing_amount) / 1000000.0, 3) AS total_revenue_millions,
    ROUND(AVG(billing_amount), 2) AS avg_claim,
    RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(billing_amount) DESC) AS revenue_rank
FROM healthcare
WHERE billing_flag = 'normal'
GROUP BY insurance_provider
ORDER BY total_revenue_millions DESC;
```
Views (`04_views.sql`) — 6 Reusable Views
View	Purpose
`vw_executive_kpis`	Power BI Page 1 — KPI card data
`vw_diagnosis_cost_summary`	Condition-level cost + outcome metrics
`vw_insurer_performance`	Revenue, volume, avg claim per insurer
`vw_monthly_admission_trends`	Time-series data for line charts
`vw_high_billing_patients`	Top 10% billing patient list
`vw_patient_demographics`	Age, gender, condition breakdown
---
📊 Power BI Dashboard
4-page interactive dashboard · 40+ DAX measures · 6 cross-page slicers
Page	Title	Key Visuals
1	🏠 Executive Summary	KPI cards, condition pie, YoY line, revenue bar
2	🦠 Diagnosis Overview	Frequency bar, test results stacked, seasonality heatmap, treemap
3	💰 Financial Performance	Insurer revenue, billing scatter, high-cost table, cost/day bar
4	👥 Patient Demographics	Age group bar, gender donut, blood type heatmap, day-of-week bar
Sample DAX Measures
```dax
Total Revenue     = CALCULATE(SUM(healthcare[billing_amount]), healthcare[billing_flag] = "normal")
Abnormal Rate %   = DIVIDE([Abnormal Count], [Total Patients]) * 100
Revenue YoY %     = DIVIDE([Total Revenue] - [Revenue PY], [Revenue PY]) * 100
Revenue PY        = CALCULATE([Total Revenue], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(healthcare[admission_date]))
Condition Rank    = RANKX(ALL(healthcare[medical_condition]), [Total Revenue],, DESC)
```
